+# LOB Pressure Dashboard (P92)
+
+Files:
+- `lob_pressure_p92.json` — Grafana dashboard (Prometheus datasource `${DS_PROMETHEUS}`).
+
+## Required metrics (Prometheus)
+Produced by `BookProcessor`:
+- `of_lob_queue_imbalance{symbol,level}`
+- `of_lob_queue_imbalance_mean{symbol}`
+- `of_lob_queue_imbalance_max_abs{symbol}`
+- `of_lob_queue_imbalance_slope{symbol}`
+- `of_lob_micro_mid_div_bps{symbol}`
+- `of_lob_micro_shift_bps{symbol}`
+- `of_lob_depth_slope{symbol,side}`  (side: bid|ask|imb)
+- `of_lob_depth_convexity{symbol,side}` (side: bid|ask|imb)
+- `of_lob_dw_obi{symbol}`
+- `of_lob_dw_obi_z{symbol}`
+- `of_lob_dw_obi_stability_score{symbol}`
+- `of_lob_dw_obi_stable_secs{symbol}`
+- `of_lob_dw_obi_stable{symbol}`
+
+## Import
+Grafana → Dashboards → Import → upload `lob_pressure_p92.json`.
+
+## Notes
+- `micro_mid_div_bps` and `micro_shift_bps` are signed; positive values imply bid-side pressure (microprice above mid), negative values imply ask-side pressure.
+- `dw_obi_z` is a rolling robust z-score; it is meant for **relative** anomaly detection and should be tuned per-symbol.
